node.text: Yes please! @tinatchen joins me today to discuss the #CTC and give you all of the details you’ll need to sign up — did you know that visiting www.ChildTaxCredit.gov and filling out your info ALSO qualifies you to receive any stimulus checks you might have missed due to your filing status!? — or to help your loved ones do so. This money is a game changer for ALL families. In every state. Because the quality of children’s lives isn’t partisan. Let’s go, friends!

node.text: American families are getting the support they need, starting this week. This will reduce child poverty by over 50%! Nearly all families with kids will qualify. And when families do well, the economy does well. For every $1 we invest in families, we see $8 returned into the economy. So this helps everyone. I’m deeply grateful for Congresswoman DeLauro’s work on getting this policy enacted, and deeply grateful to President Biden for prioritizing families and uplifting so many! Here we go!! Visit www.ChildTaxCredit.gov to figure out what you’ll begin receiving this month!

node.title: Talking about the Child Tax Credit with the legendary @rosa_delauro!

node.text: [CONT’D 2] Jared Yates Sexton rightly pointed out that “The entire reason we have rules to expel members of Congress is to expel members of Congress who have openly endorsed the murder of their colleagues, traffic in racist, virulent conspiracy theories, and have worked to overthrow the government.” That day? Over 140 officers injured. Two officers are dead from the attack; two from suicide. Officers without helmets sustained brain injuries. One officer has two cracked ribs and two smashed spinal discs. One officer is going to lose his eye; one was stabbed with a metal fence stake. And people like Lauren Boebert gave tours?! Greene says these are patriots?? Ted Cruz spoke at the rallies screaming “don’t go quietly!!” Madison Cawthorn told supporters “you can threaten” your reps over the election. Don’t even get me started on Josh Hawley. And these are the same people, who despite having facts about @ayannapressley’s panic buttons having been ripped out of her Congressional office ahead of the attack, despite the published evidence that Christopher Miller, Trump's then-acting defense secretary, on Jan 4 issued a memorandum stating that authorities at the Capitol were not allowed to use weapons, wear helmets or body armor, interact physically with protestors, employ riot control agents, or even make arrests, essentially guaranteeing that the insurrection would succeed, want to move on!? You’re damn right I agree with Rep @jackiespeier that inciting insurrection and being a terrorist sympathizer in the halls of Congress or the Senate means you should be labeled as such. But what Breitbart did, falsely claiming I am “advocating for labeling [ALL] Republicans as terrorists,” misrepresenting my agreement with Congressional leaders about the standard to which their colleagues are held and obfuscating my point to claim I’m apparently passing judgment on anyone who’s ever voted as a registered conservative? It’s egregious and irresponsible. It lacks context or the critical thinking skills required to make nuanced points. But the thing is?? They know that. “News” editors do pay attention, and do know what the argument is. [CONT]

node.text:
My sweet sweet Markie… I don’t have the words. Devastated comes to mind. Crushed. Heartbroken. This woman. This ray of sunshine. Pure light. And goodness.

Markie Post was a TV icon. Bold. Funny. Always in on the joke, usually before the rest of the room. Always holding a deeper perspective on a character’s reality than what was on the page.

When I lived in a box that made it deeply difficult to be a woman who could exist as one … and … breathe? Markie came in with arms to envelop me and eyes that fired both kindness and lightning storms into the room as she held me, and likewise called other women into her safe space. She did it all with a smile and a laugh, and with more wisdom than most of us could ever hope to learn or muster.

I loved her on Night Court. I blushed when she came to Chicago. To play MY onscreen mom!? And I loved her in our hair and makeup trailer and at cozy dinners over endless laughter and as I watched her eyes light up when she spoke of her husband and her daughters. When she called me an “uncommon woman” I melted.

Markie was the kind of set momma who made you feel invincible and gave you permission to be vulnerable and tender. I’ll never forget that mystical power. That rare duality.

We spoke about getting each of our overlapping onscreen families together. @hilarieburton, @tylerhilton, and @meganparkithere. That overlap!? We LOVED how lucky we’d been to share two TV families. And then life, different locations, and a pandemic got in the way. I will forever curse the missed opportunity of that reunion dinner we hadn’t had just yet.

Hug the people you love. Don’t say “we’ll do it soon, honey.” Dont wait until everyone is “back in town and it’s easy.” Do it now. Make the trek. Don’t miss your moments.

To her family? Michael. Kate. Daisy. The ones she lit UP when she spoke of? The ones who put a twinkle and a sparkle in her eye? Man oh man she loved you. Man oh man am I sorry to see her go. How grateful I am that you shared her with me. That I got to borrow her and her boundless heart. Thank you, forever.

#MarkiePost #MyForeverBunny ♥️🐰💔

node.text:
“Time is a gift,” a wise friend said to me.

Over the last year and a half, time has come at a cost for so many. The pandemic has been hard on countless people. Women especially, and women of color most. 

“In the wake of the COVID-19 pandemic, tens of millions of women around the world have departed the workforce, while also shouldering the brunt of unpaid labor, including schooling and caring for family members.

Of the 1.1 million Americans who were pushed out of the workforce during COVID, 80% of them were women. Disproportionately, they were Black and Brown women. And studies show it may take 2 years longer than men to return to pre-pandemic rates of employment,” explains @mspackyetti.

So how can we begin showing up for each other immediately, as we maintain pressure with our advocacy so that policy solutions can be enacted?

For her 40th birthday, Meghan, The Duchess of Sussex, had an idea. She asked 40 activists, artists, storytellers, leaders, and friends to each commit at least 40 minutes of mentorship to support women reentering the workforce. 

I’m thrilled to support Meghan, Brittany, @genevievejroth, and more women that I adore by donating my time — albeit a few days late! Doing some life things at the moment! — If you are able to do the same? Please join us in showing up. It matters. Let’s put some compassion in action. 

#40x40 #CompassionInAction | visit archewell.com/40x40 for more.

The incomparable @coribush has been sleeping outside the Capitol to raise awareness for the folks who will be displaced without a continuation of the #evictionmoratorium. She knows that pain. Cori was once a nurse living in her car, & now she’s in Congress to fight for folks like her. The idea that our leaders are going home without an answer?? That Kavanaugh has knee-capped SCOTUS to tie the hands of the President? For what? To put already at risk people at more risk in an ongoing pandemic with a variant wave that’s 1000% times more infectious than the first one that’s killed >600,000 Americans!? This is unconscionable.

・・・@katiegrossbard:

🚨 A nationwide eviction moratorium is set to expire Saturday night after @potus + Democrats in Congress failed to align on a long-shot strategy to prevent millions of Americans from being forced from their homes during a COVID-19 surge.

🏠 More than 3.6 million Americans are at risk of eviction, some in a matter of days, as nearly $47 billion in federal housing aid to the states during the pandemic has been slow to make it into the hands of renters and landlords owed payments. The moratorium expires at midnight.

🏛 Tensions mounted late Friday as it became clear there was no resolution in sight. Hours before the ban was set to expire, Biden called on local governments to “take all possible steps” to immediately disburse the funds. Evictions could begin as soon as Monday.

⚖️ On a 5-4 vote last month, the Supreme Court allowed the broad eviction ban to continue through the end of July. One of those in the majority, Justice Brett Kavanaugh, made clear he would block any additional extensions unless there was “clear and specific congressional authorization.” Biden said Thursday that the administration’s hands are tied after the Supreme Court signaled the moratorium would only be extended until the end of the month.

🗣 At the @WhiteHouse, deputy press secretary Karine Jean-Pierre said the administration backs the congressional effort “to extend the eviction moratorium to protect these vulnerable renters & their families.”

BELIEVE 💛💙💛 #FootballisLife
Still wearing this smile from last week, thanks to #TedLasso. @vdoozer and co? Thank you for the supreme joy this year. We all needed it. The sheer GOODNESS! It’s delightful.

It was a thrill to celebrate with my @weareangelcity ⚽️ family and to feel the ever-growing LA excitement!

And thank you to the #COVIDsafetyTeam who not only required proof of vaccination to attend this outdoor screening, but also tested each and every one of us prior to entry to make sure that no one was at risk of a #deltavariant breakthrough case. Your efforts made us feel safe. And that feeling has been in short supply these last eighteen months. The healthcare teams? We see you and we’re so grateful for you.

And thank you to the team who poured me into this dress and a pair of heels. I almost forgot how to walk in those. But damn. This sure was fun. @britelkin @brockcollection @jimmychoo @carlyxhair @carissaferreri @efcollection @jenmeyerjewelry #WeAreAngelCity #AngelCityFC #LosAngeles #Soccer #TheRealFootball

node.text:
Went for a walk to relish in the sunshine.
Realized the tree and I had the same idea.
Sat for a while, watching Maggie check out passers 
by, catching up on things including sweet notes from all of you.
Knowing that you’re learning and growing with @workinprogress, and all sorts of nostalgic 
and girl-powered and coming-home with @dramaqueensoth?
I just couldn’t ask for more.
What a moment.
I’m grateful for the sun and for each of you and 
your light.
Positively basking.
Love 🌹
